Git:
1) working directory
2) stage directory -git add
3) local directory --git commit


Clone repo on your local machine:

git init --initialise git 
#git config --global user.name "Nikhil Yadav"
#git config --global user.email "nikhil.yadav@blazeclan.com"

#git config --global --list 
	verify your configs


#touch sample.txt
git add sample.txt
	will add sample.txt only
#touch a b c d 
#git add . 
	Will add all the files
#git commit -m "first commit"
	enter commit for your changes

#git push -u origin master
